HTML PART 4 NOTES:
OUTLINE:
  #HTML CSS
    - Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) is used to format the layout of a webpage.
    - Anything applied to parent class is going to apply to all children elements within parent.
      - Ex: blue to body -> blue to headings,paragraphs, and other text elements within the body unless you specify something else. 
    Adding CSS to HTML:
      Inline - by using the style attribute inside HTML elements
      Internal - by using the <style> element into the <head> section
      External - by using a <link> element to link to an external CSS file
      **Most Common way is to keep CSS in external file**
    INLINE EXAMPLE:
      <h1 style="color:blue;">A Blue Heading</h1>
      <p style="color:red;">A red paragraph.</p>
    INTERNAL EXAMPLE:
        <!DOCTYPE html>
        <html>
        <head>
        <style>
        body {background-color: powderblue;}
        h1   {color: blue;}
        p    {color: red;}
        </style>
        </head>
        <body>
    EXTERNAL EXAMPLE: **To use an external style sheet, add a link to it in the <head> section of each HTML page**
        <!DOCTYPE html>
        <html>
        <head>
          <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
        </head>
        <body>
        
        <h1>This is a heading</h1>
        <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
        
        </body>
        </html>

      style.css: 
          body {
            background-color: powderblue;
          }
          h1 {
            color: blue;
          }
          p {
            color: red;
          }
    EXTERNAL_EXTENDED INFORMATION:
        CSS BORDER:
          p {
              border: 2px solid powderblue;
            }
        CSS PADDING:
            p {
              border: 2px solid powderblue;
              padding: 30px;
            }
        CSS MARGIN:
            p {
              border: 2px solid powderblue;
              margin: 50px;
            }
        LINK TO EXTERNAL CSS: 
            - SAME FOLDER:
                <head>
                  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
                </head>
            - DIFFERENT FOLDER:
                <head>
                  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/html/styles.css">
                </head>
