  #HTML FAVICON: A favicon image is displayed to the left of the page title in the browser tab.
  <head>
    <title>My Page Title</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/images/favicon.ico">
  </head>
  <body>

  FAVICON FILE SUPPORT FORMAT FOR EACH BROWSER:
    EDGE -  YES ->  ICO | PNG | GIF | JPEG | SVG
    CHROME - YES ->  ICO | PNG | GIF | JPEG | SVG
    FIREFOX - YES  ->  ICO | PNG | GIF | JPEG | SVG
    OPERA - YES ->  ICO | PNG | GIF | JPEG | SVG
    SAFARI - YES ->  ICO | PNG | GIF | JPEG | SVG
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  #HTML PAGE TITLE
    GOOD TITLE REQUIREMENTS:
      The <title> element:    
        - defines a title in the browser toolbar
        - provides a title for the page when it is added to favorites
        - displays a title for the page in search engine-results
